<normalizedToken id="53AE31E695064AC48782749A170AC0D2" originalValue="Südalpen-Witwenblume" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">Suedalpen-Witwenblume</normalizedToken>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="E51A4E4F80C263D28AAFF8C679D88C50" pageId="null" pageNumber="348" type="description">
<paragraph id="FF3FEBF6D63F2CDBAF7EF21C5C9364F0" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="27251C1CAA0431412B82BBC8DC1FAB65" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Knautia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dipsacales" pageId="null" pageNumber="348" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arvensis">
<emphasis id="CF32BA102237F3C3F65434FDD5680709" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">K. arvensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 3) durch folgende Merkmale: 25-70 cm hoch; Stengel auch im untern Teil mit 0,1-0,5 mm langen, 
<normalizedToken id="61A1BEEC5C10C197FD0733CB25BE0E95" originalValue="weißen" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">weissen</normalizedToken>
Haaren (oft nur wenige Haare), im obern Teil zudem meist mit 0,1-0,4 mm langen 
<normalizedToken id="D6895CB803C95AA93C0B64482AE9838B" originalValue="Drüsenhaaren" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">Druesenhaaren</normalizedToken>
; 
<emphasis id="2D10F05137C09217A7D1F785AD39048E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">
<normalizedToken id="AACAA3C6ECC57E78CBC5B4228F3E935A" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
oberseits zerstreut und
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="77576CFA0ED08D8FAE53B06DB7F78B0F" originalValue="±" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">+/-</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="05BDEEBA0690D35AD81C3C65AD9AABF9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">anliegend, unterseits dicht behaart</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="C01BA4A221A038C25383480B4049B217" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">Haare 0,8</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="95A4AC779848C242193FE0DA755483FB" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">1,5 mm lang</emphasis>
)
<emphasis id="5E0E71D6910B0351A5A737599CD467D6" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">
; mittlere 
<normalizedToken id="80DB7B5C8F88F77461BEFC111CD4D4B8" originalValue="Stengelblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">Stengelblaetter</normalizedToken>
ungeteilt oder zumindest bei einem Teil der Individuen einer Population jederseits mit 1
</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="F22C9AA5314EE6262261C95E06416665" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">5 seitlichen Abschnitten; Endabschnitt meist mindestens 2mal so breit wie die seitlichen Abschnitte.</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="61FACACAF8BBAB183F06BDECF9563245" originalValue="Äußere" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">Aeussere</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="6DF51B362B08B869A8E761D9384C3C42" originalValue="Hüllblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">Huellblaetter</normalizedToken>
meist etwa 3mal so lang wie breit; Kelch am Grunde mit 0,3-1 mm langen feinen Haaren; Krone meist hellpurpurn; 
<normalizedToken id="C15E1F0474066CCFFA9C6EBE087912B1" originalValue="Früchte" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">Fruechte</normalizedToken>
3,5-4,5 mm lang, mit 0,5-1 mm langen Haaren. - 
<normalizedToken id="51947B38174BE3F1AF701920AB23A88A" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5134587DF3BD3B4590FE081648B15D87" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">
<emphasis id="06FEAF4783C26243F0D73E162215C401" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="70E89F81517CF0D07345D4333D7A1C90" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">40:</emphasis>
Material von 2 Stellen an der Grigna am Comersee (Ehrendorfer 1962).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7F0147210BEB2B0C07728F518C9EAFD3" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">
<emphasis id="BD18D54986C44E0F2874050E3C6E26DC" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin, montan und subalpin. 
<normalizedToken id="754BE9D274647D24AA1C3C5A76BDC325" originalValue="Mäßig" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">Maessig</normalizedToken>
trockene, lockere, kalkhaltige 
<normalizedToken id="B0EDAB6D96342B91237B7414602CDF11" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">Boeden</normalizedToken>
in 
<normalizedToken id="006460B3754FAB118075001685A7705C" originalValue="wärmeren" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">waermeren</normalizedToken>
Lagen. Wiesen, grasige 
<normalizedToken id="9DF3C2C272589B7462EFFB823E0A5DF8" originalValue="Hänge" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">Haenge</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="5298B25B20C45415C350E551BDC75B38" originalValue="Gebüsche" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">Gebuesche</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7F5D72916F06041BAF781A5EBBA9A255" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">
<emphasis id="D0DB0E6D126032B81E5E86748F1458A2" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">Verbreitung. Insubrische Pflanze:</emphasis>
Luganersee- und Comerseegebiet, Bergamasker Alpen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6DC2193C0A517CD48DF2D41FA1509EFC" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">
<emphasis id="E49F8B48D4DCE9DA8804D94EE4C0514D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">
Bemerkungen. 
<taxonomicName id="B84B17421A15F5933A3DFCEDC6244032" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Knautia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dipsacales" pageId="null" pageNumber="348" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="transalpina">K. transalpina</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
ist wahrscheinlich hybridogenen Ursprungs, wobei 
<taxonomicName id="2D9CF6A02AC5794B046ED818B5334013" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Knautia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dipsacales" pageId="null" pageNumber="348" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longifolia">
<emphasis id="E85AD5A8AB0DF2A63FCA6390F333C148" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">K. longifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 7) und 
<taxonomicName id="F88C39FB274142E288CD9889CF60C514" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Knautia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dipsacales" pageId="null" pageNumber="348" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis id="349B78C81E88E56F84D789FBDA49EB86" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">K. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 6) beteiligt sind. Die Abgrenzung gegen 
<taxonomicName id="1FE0140D43E4C91A73D1A218E26906A2" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Knautia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dipsacales" pageId="null" pageNumber="348" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="velutina">
<emphasis id="2897207E53AB6B2ADD5ADD80BDAA174E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">K. velutina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ist im einzelnen noch weiter zu 
<normalizedToken id="BB5F27FCE0A39038504F9462FC9DD8E9" originalValue="prüfen" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">pruefen</normalizedToken>
. 
<normalizedToken id="85ABD6BFE946FAA77AAC9FA5A590088C" originalValue="Über" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">Ueber</normalizedToken>
die Stellung von 
<taxonomicName id="43C9A389DAD4CAEAD7246EB1FEC6655B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Knautia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dipsacales" pageId="null" pageNumber="348" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="transalpina">
<emphasis id="A2818D94E545CA1ACCDFF09C4087FF63" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="348">K. transalpina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vgl. auch Kunz (1939).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
